title: The memorial of the Honduras merchants, to the Committee of Lloyds. For the registry of British & foreign shipping, 25th. August, 1846, praying the removal of the existing limitations to the general use of mahogany in the building of vessels of the highest class, with an appendix, containing the representations on the same subject of various dealers & importers of mahogany, as well as of ship-owners and ship-builders in all parts of the United Kingdom
author: Honduras Merchants' Committee
